                                <p id="p0">The Shoulder Slope is the measurement of degrees at which the shoulder is sloped downwards with the HPS as the origin point. There are three methods to determine the shoulder slope measurement, the selfie method, the goniometer method or the ruler method. </p> &nbsp;

                                <h2><u>Selfie Method (Most accurate) </u></h2> &nbsp;
                                
                                <p id="p0">This method will be the easiest and most accurate way to measure shoulder slope. Have your model stand straight with her arms down. Stand directly in front and parallel to your model. Take a picture of your model, does not have to be their full height but must have their shoulders in the shot. Open your model’s picture in your CAD drafting program. You will now need to draft a horizontal line that extends from the HPS to the shoulder point. The line must extend 180 degrees or 0 Degrees from the HPS. Rotate the line, using the shoulder point as the origin, and continue the rotation until the end of line reaches the shoulder point. Record the angle of rotation. </p> &nbsp;
                                
                                <h2><u>The Ruler Method (Shoulder Drop) </u></h2>&nbsp;
