                                <p id="p0">Position a ruler horizontally at the HPS level and measure the vertical distance at the shoulder point. </p> &nbsp;
                                
                                <p id="p0">To take the shoulder slope using the ruler method, you will be measuring the shoulder drop. The shoulder drop is the vertical distance between HPS level and shoulder point level. It is best to use two rulers when measuring shoulder drop. First, you must place one end of the ruler at  HPS level and extend the ruler horizontally towards the shoulder point, ensuring the ruler remains perpendicular to the HPS (imagine a straight line extending outwards from the HPS point). Next, you will take the second ruler and measure vertically from the shoulder point to where the two rulers intersect. Once you have that measurement, input the shoulder drop measurement into the calculator to determine shoulder slope.</p> &nbsp;
           
    

