                                <p id="p0">The Armscye depth measurement is the basis for what will form the armhole. Given that arms move, we want to measure the armscye with a bit of ease to account for range of motion. </p> &nbsp;

                                <p id="p0">To take the Armscye depth, you will have your model use two or three fingers (the more depth we add, the larger the armhole will become) and place them under their armpit. From the back, when your model turns around, you will need to see the tips of their fingertips. From the tip of the bottom finger, while using your soft tape measure as a guide, extend the tape measure horizontally from the bottom finger to Center Back. The tape measure must remain parallel to the floor. At the point where the tape measure intersects the Center Back line, mark a point. Once you’ve marked the armscye depth point at Center Back, you will take the vertical measurement between the Nape landmark point and the newly marked Armscye point. </p> &nbsp;
                                
